<TITLE> Police arrest 5 in Narayanganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 6 (bdnews24.com)  Police on Thursday arrested five persons on different charges from Narayanganj. Akthar Hossain, 30, sentenced to life in prison, who had been absconding, was arrested from Jogardia village of Araihazar early Thursday. Criminals had chopped dead Abdul Latif in front of witnesses with sharp weapons at Mardasadi village of Araihazar upazila in 2004. The court sentenced gave capital punishment to five accused and life term to 21. Akthar Hossain had been absconding for a long time. In another incident, locals detained an imam of a mosque named Abdus Sattar, 45, for having an illicit relationship with a 45 year old mother of eight children at Fawsa of Araihazar upazila on Wednesday night. The locals handed him over to the police. Sattar, son of Abdul Mannan of Topsadi village Sadasadi Union of the same upazila, is the imam of Chhoto Fawsa Jame Mosque. He used to stay at a rented house of Abdul Hai. The locals said that the divorcee woman had an illicit relationship with Sattar and sometimes stayed with him at night. They claimed to have caught the two red handed in their act. In Narayanganj, a special branch of detective police arrested three youths when they were harassing female students in front of Narayanganj Government Girls' High School at Masdair area on the Sher-e-Bangla road. Mainur Rahman, of the district detective police, said that the police was patrolling in front of the girls' high school on Thursday noon. The youths were harassing the girls playing music on their mobile phones during tiffin. The police arrested Al Amin, 19, son of Harun-Or-Rashid, Ratan Mia, 19, son of Nur Islam Mia and Sujan Chandra Das, 22, son of Bijen Chandra Das of Isdair area of Fatulla. A case was underway. RAB-11 on Tuesday arrested six youths for harassing women. The court sentenced them to prison for a week. bd
